# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL CONFIGURATION FILE
# =============================================================================
# 
# ⚠️  THIS FILE IS COMPLETELY OPTIONAL!
# 
# The worker runs perfectly with ZERO configuration using sensible defaults
# and QuickChart's free tier. Only create a .env file if you want to:
#
# 1. Increase QuickChart rate limits with an API key
# 2. Add MCP authentication
# 3. Customize default values
#
# =============================================================================

# QuickChart.io API Configuration (OPTIONAL)
# ------------------------------------------
# Get your API key from: https://quickchart.io/pricing/
# The FREE tier is used by default (no key needed)
# Only add this if you need higher rate limits
# QUICKCHART_API_KEY=your_quickchart_api_key_here

# MCP Authentication (OPTIONAL)
# ------------------------------
# Set this to require API key for MCP endpoints
# Leave unset for no authentication (default)
# MCP_API_KEY=your_mcp_api_key_here

# Worker Configuration (OPTIONAL - has defaults)
# -----------------------------------------------
# All these variables have built-in defaults shown below
# Uncomment and modify only if you want to change them

# MAX_TABLE_SIZE=10000
# DEFAULT_IMAGE_FORMAT=png
# DEFAULT_IMAGE_WIDTH=800
# DEFAULT_IMAGE_HEIGHT=600
# RATE_LIMIT=60
# ENABLE_CORS=true
# LOG_LEVEL=info
# ENVIRONMENT=development

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
#
# FOR ONE-CLICK DEPLOY:
# ---------------------
# Just click the deploy button in README.md - NO .env file needed!
#
# FOR CLI DEPLOY:
# ---------------
# Option 1: Deploy with defaults (recommended)
#   npm run deploy
#
# Option 2: Deploy with custom configuration
#   1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
#   2. Edit .env with your values
#   3. Set secrets: echo "your-key" | npx wrangler secret put QUICKCHART_API_KEY
#   4. Deploy: npm run deploy
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# • Never commit .env to version control (already in .gitignore)
# • For production, use Wrangler secrets instead of .env:
#     npx wrangler secret put QUICKCHART_API_KEY
#     npx wrangler secret put MCP_API_KEY
# • Secrets are encrypted and never exposed in logs
#
# =============================================================================
